Forecaster Kgolofelo Mahlangu says temperatures are expected to rise on Monday, with Pretoria reaching up to 34&#176;C. JOHANNESBURG The South African Weather Service says Gauteng residents will experience warm weather this New Year weekend, with a 30% chance of showers and thundershowers.It says despite a Christmas weekend of heavy rains and flash floods in Gauteng and other parts of the country, residents will be able to welcome 2017 with warm weather.Forecaster Kgolofelo Mahlangu says temperatures are expected to rise on Monday, with Pretoria reaching up to 34 C.She says there are no warnings issued for the province for the New Year weekend. At the moment we don t have any alerts nothing of significance, except that over the Tshwane area it is going to get quite hot. So far we are sitting in the warm category, and on Monday and Sunday we are moving into the hot category. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)